issues.description: The original version of tas (2m air temperature) computation contains instabilities, see details here: https://errata.es-doc.org/static/view.html?uid=fabc475c-b22f-6162-89ca-345d8fdc97ce. Those instabilites also affect the diagnostic of the relative and specific humidity at the surface. For the simulations for which hurs and huss is available, and in view of the very small number of events, an a posteriori correction will be done. Meanwhile, the affected datasets have been unpublished and ongoing publications won't include hurs and huss data at higher frequencies than monthly.
issues.title: Instabilities which lead to erroneous values of tas also lead to erroneous values of hurs and huss

issues.description:
Several files with an instantaneous time axis have useless time boundaries.
Time bounds are equivalent to time axis values. Consequently, temporal means are not affected.

issues.description: Area calculations formula in metadata variable "comment" is incorrect and should be fixed.
issues.title: Error in variable "comment" metadata

issues.description: The original version of tas (2m air temperature) computation contains instabilities. Typically, a few tens of "events" occur during one year over the full globe in which tas suddenly increases by ~ 50 to 100K over one physics time-step (15 minutes long). It creates occasionally erroneous values of tasmax (error of the order 50 to 100 K) and tas (errors 1/96 times smaller, 96 being the number of time steps per day). For the simulations for which tasmax is available, and in view of the very small number of events, an a posteriori correction will be done when both tas and tasmax are available. Meanwhile, the affected datasets have been unpublished and ongoing publications won't include tas and tasmax data at higher frequencies than monthly.
issues.title: tas instabilities lead to erroneous values of tasmax

issues.description: Variable albisccp has data in % instead of fraction though units metadata indicates fraction(="1"). According to Data Request ver. 01.00.27 it should be in fraction.
issues.title: albisccp erroneous data units

issues.description: realm value in netCDF attributes has to be changed from ocnBgChem to ocnBgchem to comply with the CMIP6 specifications
issues.title: Wrong realm ocnBgChem typo

issues.description: abrupt-4xCO2 run has been extended adding 500 simulated years as a second extension.
issues.title: 300 years second extension for abrupt-4xCO2

issues.title: 200 years extension for piControl

issues.description: Due to an old version of dr2xml, 3D ocean files of several IPSL-CM6 simulations have a depth dimension with a wrong name that should be "olevel" instead of "depth*".
issues.title: Wrong depth dimension name

issues.description: piControl run has been extended adding 500 simulated years.
issues.title: 500 years extension for piControl

issues.title: o3 incorrect unit attribute

issues.description: piControl variable Eday/zg was substituted for expand time range. Data/metadata was not changed.
issues.title: piControl variable Eday/zg

issues.description: An error in the monthly and daily averages of albisccp/pctisccp was detected in CNRM-CM6-1/CNRM-ESM2-1 output. These time-means were not weighted by the ISCCP Total Cloud Fraction (cltisccp).
issues.title: Error in albisccp and pctisccp variables

issues.description: The "historical" member r2i1p1f1 ran with an old version of dr2xml. 3D ocean files have a depth dimension with a wrong name that should be "olevel" instead of "depth*".
issues.title: Wrong depth dimension name in historical member r2

issues.description: Four CMIP6 variables set as "fixed" actually are time-dependent due to the grid of the ocean model NEMO. As the volume of ocean grid cells and sea ice cover are time dependent, the fixed variables masscello, thkcello, deptho and sftof are also time dependent hence cannot be provided as static variables. Those variables should not have been published and have been retracted.
issues.title: "Fixed" CMIP6 variables provided by NEMO model are time-dependent

issues.description: sidmassevapsubl, sndmasssnf and  was improperly computed, resulting in erroneous values
issues.title: sidmassevapsubl was improperly computed, resulting in erroneous values

issues.description: Because the contribution of open water and ice dynamics to ice growth does not vanish when the ice is very thick, the ice thickness can grow to very large values, probably unrealistic, in very cold climates such as the one induced by a 4% decrease in the solar constant. Besides, an unfortunate choice of the upper ice category limit induces a leak of water for such ice thicknesses, hence the water balance is not closed in this simulation. This leads to a fast decrease in the total volume of the ocean. Part of it is due to the water leak, and the rest is due to a rebalancing of some of the water reservoirs.
issues.title: Ice thickness growing to very large values

issues.description: There are 2 problems with selected annual ocean output files that were formed from monthly data.  First the annual averages were calculated from January through November instead of January through December. Second, the days of the month were not taken into account when calculating the annual average.
issues.title: Annual files of ocean output incorrectly averaged.

issues.description: Due to a model configuration error, tasmin and tasmax were erroneously calculated as averages instead of minima and maxima. The affected files will not be replaced, but a formula will be provided to the community to approximate the tasmin and tasmax values from existing variables. The formula will be posted here and on the CESM website once it is tested and devised.
issues.title: tasmin and tasmax have identical values at daily and monthly timescales

issues.description: Within the conversion from CESM's CAM precipitation units (m s-1) to CMIP's units of (kg m-2 s-1) an incorrect scaling factor was applied. The conversion should have been to multiply CAM's values by 1000 kg m-3. Instead, the values were multiplied by 1000 and then divided by 86400, resulting in values that are too small.
issues.title: pr and prc have incorrect values at daily and monthly timescales due to an incorrect scaling factor

issues.description: Incorrect some coordinates and cell_methods in piControl ocean, seaIce variables
issues.title: Incorrect some coordinates and cell_methods in piControl ocean, seaIce variables

issues.description: Variable tslsi (3hr,day) has incorrect "comment" variable attribute. It should be completely removed.
issues.title: Variable tslsi (3hr,day) has incorrect "comment" variable attribute

issues.description: Due to a minor misconfiguration of our data processing system daily data on model levels in the CFday MIP table has been produced in excessively large files (up to ~170 GB). In order to minimise potential data management and analysis issues for all concerned we have withdrawn these files and will re-publish them in more manageable files in due course.
issues.title: Withdrawal of excessively large files for daily data on model levels

issues.description: During land cover transition, 14C and 13C root carbon that should be transferred into 14C and 13C litter pools is mistakenly transferred to the bulk C litter pool.  This has effectively no impact on bulk C or anything downstream in the coupled system. It affects 13C and 14C soil C, litter C, root C, and soil respiration in simulations where there has been land cover change.
issues.title: 13C and 14C soil C, litter C, root C, and soil respiration are incorrect in simulations with land cover change

issues.description: The final version of RFMIP protocol requires Present-day (year 2014) Ozone Concentrations as a forcing for piClim-antro experiment. This 4-member ensemble was run using preindustrial Ozone values (the same as in piClim-control experiment), as initially specified on ES-DOC: "Constant pre-industrial tropospheric and stratospheric ozone climatology. Models without interactive ozone chemistry should specify the pre-industrial ozone fields from a data set produced from a pre-industrial control simulation that uses 1850 emissions and a mean solar forcing averaged over solar cycles 8-10, representative of the mean mid-19th century solar forcing." The simulations will be (re-)published as "r*i1p1f2", to indicate a different forcing than the one required by the protocol.
issues.title: Wrong ozone forcing for piClim-anthro experiment

issues.description: The final version of RFMIP protocol requires Present-day (year 2014) Ozone Concentrations as a forcing for piClim-spAer-antro experiment. This 4-member ensemble was run using preindustrial Ozone values (the same as in piClim-control experiment), as initially specified on ES-DOC: "Constant pre-industrial tropospheric and stratospheric ozone climatology. Models without interactive ozone chemistry should specify the pre-industrial ozone fields from a data set produced from a pre-industrial control simulation that uses 1850 emissions and a mean solar forcing averaged over solar cycles 8-10, representative of the mean mid-19th century solar forcing." The simulations will be (re-)published as "r*i1p1f2", to indicate a different forcing than the one required by the protocol.
issues.title: Wrong ozone forcing for piClim-spAer-anthro experiment

issues.description: ssp245 simulations started from the historical r2i1p1f1 run. The "parent_variant_label" attribute should be corrected accordingly from "r1i1p1f1" to "r2i1p1f1".
issues.title: Wrong parent variable label in ssp245 (r2i1p1f1)

issues.description: The 3rd land unit type dimension (urban) was computed incorrectly.
issues.title: Urban land unit type incorrect

issues.description: An incorrect definition was used to create the cSoilLevels variable, resulting in yearly timesteps being provided in a monthly file.  The values in these fields are correct, they just needed to be replicated 12 times each.
issues.title: cSoilLevels files are missing timesteps

issues.description:
Due to a mistaken version upgrade, some files disappeared from one version to another.
The period have been republish under a new dataset version.
issues.title: Missing sub-periods

issues.description: ccb (air pressure at convective cloud base) was originally diagnosed as the level where vertical convective mass flux equaled zero.  Because the convective mass flux below cloud base can be nonzero, this diagnostic is not appropriate for ccb.
issues.title: piControl variable Amon/ccb

issues.description: Due to a processing system error the latitude and longitude data being written to the published files is incorrect and may be up to half a degree out. Data that should have been given latitudes and longitudes corresponding to the T points of the eORCA1 grid was instead given coordinate values for the U or V points (or vice-versa) depending on processing order.  Affected data has been withdrawn and replacement data sets will be published in due course.
issues.title: Incorrect latitude & longitude coordinate data in some Omon datasets

issues.description: For models GFDL-AM4 and GFDL-CM4 and experiments amip, piControl, historical, 1pctCO2, abrupt-4xCO2, and ssp585, ssp245, monthly mean datasets in Amon incorrectly identify the frequency as "monC" (monthly climatology computed from monthly mean samples) when it should be "mon" (monthly mean samples).
issues.title: Wrong "frequency" global attribute for some monthly mean datasets

issues.description: According to the Data Request, Amon/sbl (surface snow and ice sublimation flux) should include contributions from land and sea-ice snow/ice. This variable was saved from the land model and so does not include contribution from sea-ice. As it does not match the Data Request, this dataset should not be used.
issues.title: Incorrect Amon/sbl

issues.description: When constructing the siitdconc variable, a conversion factor(*100) was incorrectly applied twice.
issues.title: siitdconc values incorrect

issues.description: The definition of field vt100 as requested in CMIP6 Data Request version 01.00.21 (used for all runs) is "Northward Heat Flux due to Eddies" ; it was overlooked, which resulted in the publication of a field which is a raw temperature advection (i.e. a raw product of temperature and northward wind component); furthermore, the units indicated is W/m*2, which is erroneous
issues.title: variable vt100 erroneous CNRM-CM6-1 and CNRM-ESM2-1 outputs

issues.description: The published data (for all variables) include an error in the natural emissions of all species during the latter half of December 2014. Thus, all model simulation results are not valid for this time period. This dataset is being retracted and replaced by corrected results.
issues.title: Incorrect emissions in December 2014

issues.description: The calculation of co2mass was done incorrectly, due to the mass of the atmosphere not being included.
issues.title: co2mass was incorrectly calculated

issues.description: An error in the cfadDbze94 variable (Table Emon and E3hrPt) was detected in CNRM-CM6-1/CNRM-ESM2-1 output (bug within the online coupling between the model and the COSP/CloudSat Radar simulator).  The erroneous output have been removed from the ESGF archive. The amip simulations, which have produced this diagnostic, will be rerun as soon as possible with a corrected diagnostic.
issues.title: Error in cfadDbze94 variable

issues.description:
An error has been found in the calculation of fgco2, the "Surface Downward Flux of Total CO2", in that this has been reported in kg of CO2 rather than kg of carbon, i.e. the values are too large by a factor of approximately 3.67 (44/12). 

All affected datasets have been retracted.
issues.title: Incorrect calculation of Omon/fgco2 in UKESM1

issues.description: The GFDL-CM4 1pctCO2, abrupt-4xCO2, and historical experiments branched from piControl at year 251, which was 250 years (91250 days) after 0001-1-1 (piControl time-axis units). Therefore, the branch_time_in_parent is 91250, not 36500.
issues.title: Wrong branch_time_in_parent attribute for GFDL-CM4 1pctCO2, abrupt-4xCO2, and historical experiments

issues.description: The GFDL-CM4 ssp245 and ssp585 experiments start in year 2015 and the time-axis is "days since 1850". Therefore, the branch_time_in_child is 165 years (60225 days), not zero.
issues.title: Wrong branch_time_in_child for GFDL-CM4 ssp245 and ssp585

issues.description:
This only affects the r1i1p1f1 member of the EC-EARTH-CONSORTIUM ensemble (KNMI runs); the historical experiment has accidentally been started with an incorrect initial ocean condition. We will rerun the historical experiment and the scenario experiments, and publish
them when they are finalized.
issues.title: Incorrect initial ocean condition in historical experiment

issues.description: The calculation of evspsblsoi in these datasets is incorrect; it does not include the contribution from sublimation, but does include transpiration. These datasets have been withdrawn
issues.title: Incorrect calculation of Lmon/evspsblsoi in HadGEM3 and UKESM1

issues.description: Some sea ice mass budget terms were calculated incorrectly. In order to correctly calculate these terms they needed to be divided by the timestep over which they were averaged (1800 sec = 30 min). Since these variables are diagnostic output they did not affect the model integration or subsequent values calculated. In later versions of the code this error was corrected, so only output from some simulations needs correcting.
issues.title: Sea ice mass budget terms incorrectly calculated

issues.description:
The order of the bounds in the latitude coordinate has been swapped over. For example, they are:

 lat_bnds =
  -88.8206155255893, -90,
  -87.8906536323674, -88.8206155255893,

rather than:

 lat_bnds =
  -90, -88.8206155255893,
  -88.8206155255893, -87.8906536323674,

Some tools will struggle to open these files. The files will be retracted, corrected and then re-published.
issues.title: Latitude bounds order swapped

issues.description: By definition all advective mass transport processes, resolved and parameterized should be included in msftmz. Within the conversion from the CESM variable MOC to the CMIP variable msftmz, an error was made where only the Eulerian advection was included.
issues.title: Incorrect definition used for msftmz

issues.description: The file names of NorESM2-LM v20190815 output turned out to be wrong with the oder of experiment_id and source_id mixed up. The cause for this was a bug in the CMOR-ization setup. We are now retracting all NorESM2-LM CMIP6 datasets and will republish with correct file naming as soon as possible. As there was nothing wrong with neither data nor metadata we intend to keep the old version id when republish the data.
issues.title: wrong order of experiment_id and source_id in file names of NorESM2-LM v20190815 output

issues.description: A bug in post-processing caused that every second month is missing in atmospheric NorESM2-LM Emon output v20190815. The affected data has been retracted and fixed data using a new dataset version will be published soon. The affected Emon fields are hus, loadbc, loaddust, loadpoa, loadss, ps, rsdsdiff, ua, va and wap.
issues.title: missing months in atmospheric NorESM2-LM Emon output v20190815

issues.description:
A wrong unit has been fed to CMOR during the CMORisation of siarean, siareas, siextents, siextentn (MIP table SImon, respectively). This introduced the factor of 1e12 in the data. The units of the data, as published under v20190710, would be "m2" and not "1e6 km2" as is given in the files.
Affected is the first realisation r1i1p1f1 of ssp245, ssp126, ssp370 and ssp585, respectively.
issues.title: SImon siarean, siareas, siextents, siextentn: values are too high by a factor of 1e12

issues.description: The variable co2mass has been wrongly written using "ppm" instead of "kg". A new version of the affected datasets should be publish to conform to the CMIP6 requirement.
issues.title: Wrong co2mass units

issues.description: The sea-surface temperature (SST) forcing for tier 1 experiment 1.3 (piSST-pdSIC) has been updated in order to be consistent with other PAMIP experiments. After the update the SST for 1.1-1.3 is identical to 1.5-1.2 in the Northern Hemisphere and identical to 1.7-1.2 in the Southern Hemisphere. The SST for 1.3-1.2 is identical to 1.1-1.5 in the Northern Hemisphere and identical to 1.1-1.7 in the Southern Hemisphere. The SST changes are in the Arctic and Antarctic. These changes may impact the calculation for polar sea ice loss effect (1.1-1.3) and remote SST warming effect (1.3-1.2).
issues.title: Updated sea-surface temperature forcing resulted in rerun of PAMIP Tier 1 experiment 1.3

issues.description: Some ESM4 snc output was incorrectly calculated. During processing, snc reported as a fraction of land area was re-normalized to the Data Request-specified fraction of grid cell area (by multiplying by land area fraction). As a result of a processing error, some ESM4 output was normalized twice, resulting in incorrect data. Affected data will be withdrawn and republished.
issues.title: snc values incorrect

issues.description: The datasets for the r2i1p1f3, r3i1p1f3 and r4i1p1f3 ssp245 simulations contain only data for 2015-2020 to support urgent DAMIP analyses. Once the source simulations have been completed these datasets will be extended to the full range (2015-2100).
issues.title: Short datasets submitted for HadGEM3-GC31-LL ScenarioMIP ssp245 r2-r4

issues.description: The year 290 is missing in some variables of piControl simulation, becuase of a bug in post processing. The affected files will be replaced.
issues.title: year 290 is missing in some variables of piControl simulation

issues.description: The amip-piForcing experiment based on the CNRM-CM6-1 standard configuration of the CNRM model has been mistakenly initialized on January 1st 1979 (like the AMIP experiment from the DECK) and will be rerun as soon as possible starting as requested by CFMIP on January 1st 1870. This simulation has been removed from the ESGF archive.

issues.title: The values above 3 hPa pressure level in EmonZ/AERmonZ output should not be used.

issues.title: Convert climatologies to monthly time serie

issues.description:
An issue has been discovered in the sea-surface temperature (SST) forcing for experiment 1.3 (piSST-pdSIC): 
tos_input4MIPs_SSTsAndSeaIce_PAMIP_UCI-pi-prArctic-prAntarctic-1-0_gn_187001-188012-clim.nc

Experiment 1.3 was originally designed to have exact same present-day sea ice as in 1.1 and 1.4, with preindustrial SST outside of the sea ice zone and present-day SST inside the sea ice zone. However, to be consistent with other PAMIP experiments SST has to be set to preindustrial values both outside and inside the sea ice zone, i.e., the SST for 1.1-1.3 should be identical to 1.5-1.2 in the Northern Hemisphere and identical to 1.7-1.2 in the Southern Hemisphere, and the SST for 1.3-1.2 should be identical to 1.1-1.5 in the Northern Hemisphere and identical to 1.1-1.7 in the Southern Hemisphere. 

We recommend that all modeling groups download the updated 1.3 SST file tos_input4MIPs_SSTsAndSeaIce_PAMIP_UCI-pi-prArctic-prAntarctic-1-1_gn_187001-188012-clim.nc 
and rerun this simulation.
issues.title: Error in PAMIP-1.3 tos file

issues.description: Problem of reproductibility with inconsistencies between some variables (from 2059 onwards)
issues.title: Issues in ScenarioMIP ssp370 CNRM-ESM2-1 r1i1p1f2 simulation (v20190328)

issues.description: lossch4 is missing a 1.e6/6.022e23 scaling factor. It can be applied manually and the data will then be correct. lossch4 will be recalculated and the data replaced.
issues.title: Missing scaling factor from all lossch4 data.

issues.description: Problem of reproductibility with inconsistencies between some variables (from 2047 onwards)
issues.title: Issues in ScenarioMIP ssp585 CNRM-ESM2-1 r1i1p1f2 simulation (v20190328)

issues.description: As part of the unit conversion from CESM output to CMIP output a scaling factor was never applied to the co2 variable resulting in incorrect values. The original units were kg CO2 / kg dry air, and as part of the conversion to mol / mol the data should have been multiplied by the ratio of the molecular weight of dry air to the molecular weight of CO2 (28.966/44.0).
issues.title: CO2 values are incorrect due to missing scaling factor

issues.title: Published under wrong source_id
